  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7033.54 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive +12.1B gamma wall at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging posture but approaching the key resistance zone where they'll aggressively sell rallies. The PIN regime combined with the wall_break event suggests dealers just finished buying the dip below 7030 and are now positioned to cap upside momentum as we approach the 7050 strike. Watch for heavy dealer selling pressure if we push toward 7050, while any weakness back toward 7015 should see dealer buying support kick in.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get capped near 7050 with support around 7015-7030.",
